# 🚨 Violence Prediction for CCTV Surveillance Systems

> A deep learning model that automatically detects violent activity from CCTV footage using a **frozen ResNet-18 CNN + LSTM** architecture for temporal video understanding. Trained and evaluated on Kaggle with 2× GPU.

---

## 📌 Problem Statement

Manual monitoring of CCTV cameras is inefficient and error-prone — human operators miss critical incidents across large-scale infrastructure (1B+ cameras globally, ~60% incidents missed). This project automates real-time violence detection using deep learning on video frame sequences.

---

## 🧠 Model Architecture

```
Input Video Clip  →  16 frames sampled  →  (B × 16 × 3 × 224 × 224)
                              ↓
              ResNet-18 (Frozen — pretrained ImageNet weights)
                    512-d spatial feature per frame
                              ↓
                   LSTM (128 hidden units, batch_first)
                    Temporal sequence modelling
                              ↓
                         Dropout (p=0.5)
                              ↓
                     FC Layer  (128 → 1)
                              ↓
              BCEWithLogitsLoss + class-weighted sigmoid
                              ↓
                  Violence (1) / Non-Violence (0)
```

**Key design decisions:**
- ResNet-18 CNN is **fully frozen** — only LSTM + FC layers are trained
- `GroupShuffleSplit` on `video_id` prevents any frame from the same video appearing in both train and val
- `pos_weight = n_neg / n_pos` handles class imbalance in loss
- `ReduceLROnPlateau` scheduler (patience=3, factor=0.5) adapts learning rate on val accuracy
- Separate `transform_train` (flip + color jitter) and `transform_val` (clean resize only)

