## 📊 Dataset

| Split | Source | Videos | Windows (16-frame) | Label |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Violence | UCF Crime (CCTV — fights, assault, robbery) | 23 | 2,958 | 1 |
| Non-Violence | RWF-2000 (real surveillance footage) | 50 | 3,027 | 0 |
| **Total** | | **73** | **5,985** | — |

- **Train / Val split:** `GroupShuffleSplit` (80% / 20%) → **60 train videos / 15 val videos**
- **Train windows:** ~4,889 &nbsp;|&nbsp; **Val windows:** ~1,096
- **No data leakage:** video-level grouping ensures zero overlap ✅
- **Frame size:** 224 × 224, normalized with ImageNet mean/std
- **Dataset on Kaggle:** [`idkabtit/violencepredictiondataset`](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/idkabtit/violencepredictiondataset)

---

## ⚙️ ML Pipeline

| Step | Detail |
|---|---|
| **Data Loading** | Two CSVs (violence + non-violence), merged & shuffled; `frame_paths` parsed from pipe-separated or `ast.literal_eval` format |
| **Group Split** | `GroupShuffleSplit` on `video_id` — zero frame leakage between splits |
| **Augmentation** | Train: `RandomHorizontalFlip` + `ColorJitter(b=0.3, c=0.3, s=0.2)` · Val: clean resize only |
| **Feature Extraction** | Frozen ResNet-18 — 512-d vector per frame; `(B×T, C, H, W)` batch reshape |
| **Sequence Modelling** | `nn.LSTM(512, 128, batch_first=True)` — last hidden state `h_T` |
| **Prediction Head** | `Dropout(0.5)` → `FC(128→1)` → `BCEWithLogitsLoss` with `pos_weight` |
| **Optimiser** | `Adam` (LR = 1e-4, trainable params: LSTM + FC only) |
| **Scheduler** | `ReduceLROnPlateau(mode='max', patience=3, factor=0.5)` on val accuracy |

---

## 📈 Training Results

### Final Run — 25 Epochs (Frozen CNN, LR=1e-4, 2× GPU)

| Epoch | Train Loss | Val Acc | F1 |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | 142.86 | 59.49% | 0.094 |
| 2 | 86.00 | **60.86%** ← best | 0.161 |
| 5 | 45.81 | 59.03% | 0.107 |
| 10 | 25.58 | 57.30% | 0.124 |
| 15 | 18.51 | 55.20% | 0.155 |
| 22 | 15.25 | 50.55% | 0.316 |
| 25 | 16.26 | 54.20% | 0.190 |

**Best Validation Accuracy: 60.86%** (saved at Epoch 2)

> Training loss drops steadily from ~143 → ~16, but val accuracy plateaus early — consistent with a small dataset and a fully frozen feature extractor.

### Sanity Run (20 samples, 3 batches)
```
Batch 0 | Loss: 0.6020
Batch 1 | Loss: 0.6532
Batch 2 | Loss: 0.9067
✅ SANITY RUN COMPLETE
```

